HEADWORD: Unsling
<hw>Un*sling"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>sling</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To
take off the slings of, as a yard, a cask, or the like; to release from
the slings.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

